    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>Imp</abbr><ex>erator</ex></expan> Caesar <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arcus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Aurel</abbr><ex>ius</ex></expan> Commodus <lb n="2"/>Antoninus <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>ustus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>P</abbr><ex>ius</ex></expan> Germanicus Sarmaticus Brittanicus <lb n="3"/>maximus securitati provincialium suorum consulens <lb n="4"/>turres novas instituit et veteres refecit <expan><abbr>oper</abbr><ex>a</ex></expan> militum <lb n="5"/><supplied reason="lost">s</supplied>uorum curante <lb n="6"/><expan><abbr>Cl</abbr><ex>audio</ex></expan> Perpetuo <expan><abbr>proc</abbr><ex>uratore</ex></expan> suo
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Es handelt sich möglicherweise um denselben Stein wie AE 1902, 220. Datierung: nich vor 184 n. Chr. (Commodus nimmt den Beinamen Britannicus an) und vor der erneuten Annahme des praenomen Lucius durch Commodus 191 n. Chr.</p>
            </div>
